***HELPSTRINGS
ID_VPORTSJOI   [Combines two adjacent viewports into one larger viewport:  vports]
ID_VPOINT      [Sets the viewing direction for a three-dimensional visualization of the drawing:  vpoint]
ID_UCSYAXROT   [Rotates the current UCS about the Y axis:  ucs]
ID_UCSWORLD    [Sets the UCS to the World Coordinate System:  ucs]
ID_UCSICONON   [Enables the coordinate system icon:  ucsicon]
ID_THICKNESS   [Sets the current 3D thickness:  thickness]
ID_TBSURFACE   [Surfaces toolbar]
ID_TABLETON    [Turns Tablet mode on:  tablet]
ID_STRETCH     [Moves or stretches objects:  stretch]
ID_STATS       [Displays rendering statistics:  stats]
ID_PURGETXT    [Removes unused text styles from the drawing database:  purge]
ID_POINTFIYZ   [Specifies a .YZ point filter]
ID_POINTFIXY   [Specifies a .XY point filter]
ID_POINT       [Creates a point object:  point]
ID_PANRIGHT    [Moves the drawing to the right:  pan]
ID_PANLEFT     [Moves the drawing to the left:  pan]
ID_OSNAPQUIC   [Snaps to the first snap point found:  qui]
ID_MNFORMAT    [Changes the appearance or attributes of selected objects]
ID_MNEDIT      [Undo or redo a command; copy, move, or clear a selection; manage OLE objects]
ID_MLSTYLE     [Manages styles for multiple parallel lines:  mlstyle]
ID_GROUP       [Creates a named selection set of objects:  group]
ID_EXTEND      [Extends an object to meet another object:  extend]
ID_DIMRADIUS   [Creates radial dimensions for circles and arcs:  dimradius]
ID_DDUNITS     [Controls coordinate and angle display formats and determines precision:  ddunits]
ID_DDRENAME    [Changes the names of named objects:  ddrename]
ID_BREAK       [Erases parts of objects or splits an object in two:  break]
ID_ARCSTCELE   [Creates an arc using the start point, center, and length of chord:  arc]
ID_ARCCESTEN   [Creates an arc using the center, start point, and endpoint:  arc]
ID_ARC3POINT   [Creates an arc using three points:  arc]
ID_ZOOM_WINDOW_0 [Zooms to display an area specified by a rectangular window:  zoom w]
ID_VPOINTFRO   [Sets the view point to front:  vpoint]
ID_UCSXAXROT   [Rotates the current UCS about the X axis:  ucs]
ID_UCS         [Manages user coordinate systems:  ucs]
ID_TBRENDER    [Render toolbar]
ID_STYLE       [Creates named styles:  style]
ID_SOLVIEW     [Creates floating viewports using orthographic projection to lay out multi- and sectional view drawings of 3D solid and body objects:  solview]
ID_SAVEIMG     [Saves a rendered image to a file:  saveimg]
ID_PURGELIN    [Removes unused linetypes from the drawing database:  purge]
ID_PSIN        [Inserts an Encapsulated PostScript file into the current drawing:  psin]
ID_POINTFIXZ   [Specifies a .XZ point filter]
ID_MENULOAD    [Loads partial menu files:  menuload]
ID_IMAGEFRAM   [Controls whether the image frame is displayed on the screen or hidden from view:  imageframe]
ID_DRAWORDER   [Changes the display order of images and other objects:  draworder]
ID_DRAWORDEA   [Forces selected objects to be displayed in front of a reference object:  draworder]
ID_ASESQLED    [Executes Structured Query Language (SQL) statements:  asesqled]
ID_ARCCESTLE   [Creates an arc using the center, start point, and length of chord:  arc]
ID_ARC         [Creates an arc:  arc]
ID_AI_SPHERE   [Creates a spherical polygon mesh:  ai_sphere]
ID_AI_MOLC     [Makes the layer of a selected object the current layer: ai_molc]
ID_3DPOLY      [Creates a polyline of straight line segments in three-dimensional space:  3dpoly]
ID_ZOOMWINDO   [Zooms to display an area specified by a rectangular window:  zoom]
ID_ZOOMREALT   [Zooms in realtime:  zoom]
ID_ZOOMDYNAM   [Zooms to display the generated portion of the drawing:  zoom]
ID_WNEW        [Starts What's New:  wnew.exe]
ID_VPORTSSAV   [Saves the current viewport using a specified name:  vports]
ID_VPOINTTOP   [Sets the view point to top:  vpoint]
ID_VPOINTSE    [Sets the view point to southeast isometric:  vpoint]
ID_VPOINTBAC   [Sets the view point to back:  vpoint]
ID_UCSICONNO   [Displays the icon at the lower-left corner of the viewport regardless of the location of the UCS origin:  ucsicon]
ID_U           [Reverses the most recent operation:  u]
ID_TBSOLIDS    [Solids toolbar]
ID_SUBTRACT    [Creates a composite region or solid by subtraction:  subtract]
ID_SPLINEDIT   [Edits a spline object:  splinedit]
ID_SLICE       [Slices a set of solids with a plane:  slice]
ID_SETUV       [Sets and adjust material mappers on objects:  setuv]
ID_SECTION     [Uses the intersection of a plane and solids to create a region:  section]
ID_SCRIPT      [Executes a sequence of commands from a script:  script]
ID_PURGEBLK    [Removes unused blocks from the drawing database:  purge]
ID_PURGEALL    [Removes all unused objects from the drawing database:  purge]
ID_OSNAPAPPA   [Snaps to the apparent intersection of two objects:  app]
ID_MLINE       [Creates multiple parallel lines:  mline]
ID_EXPLODE     [Breaks a compound object into its component objects:  explode]
